message.content:
Neural Networks, Theory. 

Neural Networks: The paper discusses the Support Vector Machine (SVM) as an alternative training technique for Polynomial, Radial Basis Function and Multi-Layer Perceptron classifiers. It also mentions the optimization of the objective function by solving a large-scale quadratic programming problem with linear and box constraints. These are all related to neural networks.

Theory: The paper discusses the derivation of Support Vector Machines, its relationship with Structural Risk Minimization (SRM), and its geometrical insight. It also mentions the inductive principle of SRM, which aims at minimizing a bound on the generalization error of a model. These are all related to theory.
